
[1]soporific

   SOPORIF'IC, a. [L. sopor, sleep, and facio, to make.] Causing sleep;
   tending to cause sleep; narcotic; as the soporific virtues of opium.

   SOPORIF'IC, n. A medicine, drug, plant or other thing that has the
   quality of inducing sleep.
